reviews.text: Somewhat in the middle of nowhere, this isnʼt an entirely an unpleasant little station if the weatherʼs nice even though the diminutive platforms are fairly barren. However, there are no amenities and only two services in either direction actually stop here each day (one in the morning and one in the late afternoon/early evening). Trains to and from Skegness, however, pass through on a fairly regular basis so at least if you were stuck here for an extended period you could at least watch the level crossing at one end of the station occasionally spring into life.
Great station.   Only stops once in the morning and once in the evening
